summary: Killing Eve: Villanelle [ESFP]
title: Killing Eve: Villanelle [ESFP]
body:
UNOFFICIAL TYPING BY: anonymous

Extraverted Sensing (Se): Villanelle is a professional killer for one major reason: she enjoys it. The thrill of ending another person’s life, particularly in gruesome and savage ways, shakes her to her core with pleasure. Villanelle uses her money to indulge her desires with delicious food, wonderful clothing and incredible sex. She basically treats her game with Eve as a game to test the skills to their limits.

Introverted Feeling (Fi): A certain unsaid set of values and venom lurk beneath Villanelle’s exterior. Completely disconnected from what can be considered the norms of society, her attitude is alien to what the world expects from the people in it. Villanelle can be considered akin to an alien attempting to fit into human civilization.

Extraverted Thinking (Te): Villanelle can be demanding to others, to get under their skin. Her interactions with Eve bring this out of her, as she does become pushed into a corner by Eve. She feels no qualms about bluntly explaining to her victims what happens to them when they die, as they die.

Introverted Intuition (Ni): Villanelle senses something special in Eve that she can’t quite understand, but intrigues her. It binds the two of them on a path of mutual self-destruction. Her Intuition tends to get lost in the thrill of the moment, though.

summary: none of these will bring disaster [Killing Eve, Eve Polastri]
title: none of these will bring disaster [Killing Eve, Eve Polastri]
description:
“I have lost two jobs, a husband, and a best friend because of you."  But what else has Eve lost? Does she even know? (1500 words, teen)

yuletide 2018 reveal!  figuring out what i wanted to write about this universe took a long time, but it turns out what fascinates me is how fucked-up eve is.  so that was fun.
